The paper focuses on improving breast cancer detection using deep learning, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNN), which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of multi-input CNN and the incorporation of symmetry information suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and medical imaging (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for further improvement by adding temporal data, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
